tool.name: ebi_fasta

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: The base uri of the EBI web service.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Email address, reqd by EBI.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: The output format of the results

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Only the switch will be passed in the argument list.
parameter_list.helptext: Turn on debugging.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: The FASTA program to be used for the Sequence Similarity Search

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Indicates if the query sequence is protein, DNA or RNA. This prevents issues when using nucleotide sequences that contain many ambiguous residues.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: (Protein searches) The substitution matrix used for scoring alignments when searching the database.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: (Nucleotide searches) The match score is the bonus to the alignment score when matching the same base. The mismatch is the penalty when failing to match.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Score for the first residue in a gap.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Score for each additional residue in a gap.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Turn on/off the display of all significant alignments between query and library sequence.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Limits the number of scores and alignments reported based on the expectation value. This is the maximum number of times the match is expected to occur by chance.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Limit the number of scores and alignments reported based on the expectation value. This is the minimum number of times the match is expected to occur by chance. This allows closely related matches to be excluded from the result in favor of more distant relationships.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: For nucleotide sequences specify the sequence strand to be used for the search. By default both upper (provided) and lower (reverse complement of provided) strands are used, for single stranded sequences searching with only the upper or lower strand may provide better results.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Turn on/off the histogram in the FASTA result. The histogram gives a qualitative view of how well the statistical theory fits the similarity scores calculated by the program.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Maximum number of match score summaries reported in the result output.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Maximum number of match alignments reported in the result output.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Different score report formats.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: The statistical routines assume that the library contains a large sample of unrelated sequences. Options to select what method to use include regression, maximum likelihood estimates, shuffles, or combinations of these.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Specify a range or section of the input sequence to use in the search. Example: Specifying '34-89' in an input sequence of total length 100, will tell FASTA to only use residues 34 to 89, inclusive.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Specify the sizes of the sequences in a database to search against. For example: 100-250 will search all sequences in a database with length between 100 and 250 residues, inclusive.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Filter regions of low sequence complexity. This can avoid issues with low complexity sequences where matches are found due to composition rather then meaningful sequence similarity. However in some cases filtering also masks regions of interest and so should be used with caution.

parameter_list.switch_use__description: Both the switch and the value will be passed in the argument list. They will be separated joined with an equals(=) character with no spaces.
parameter_list.helptext: Accepts sequences in fasta format.

tool.description: FASTA (pronounced FAST-Aye) stands for FAST-All, reflecting the fact that it can be used for a fast protein comparison or a fast nucleotide comparison. This program achieves a high level of sensitivity for similarity searching at high speed. This is achieved by performing optimised searches for local alignments using a substitution matrix. The high speed of this program is achieved by using the observed pattern of word hits to identify potential matches before attempting the more time consuming optimised search. The trade-off between speed and sensitivity is controlled by the ktup parameter, which specifies the size of the word. Increasing the ktup decreases the number of background hits. Not every word hit is investigated but instead initially looks for segment's containing several nearby hits.
